-- 3. Chat session
INSERT INTO chat_sessions (id, user_id, org_id, title, messages, ui_state, created_at, updated_at, is_active, status, incident_id) VALUES (E'a7afc8b2-16f9-43cc-81dc-dfe41f610c3b', E'ab209180-626b-4601-8042-9f6328d03ae9', E'26db606d-1453-41be-b994-256ea1c7ee5b', E'RCA: checkout-service-oom-risk', '[{"text": "# ROOT CAUSE ANALYSIS REQUIRED - NEWRELIC ALERT\n\n## ALERT DETAILS:\n- **Title**: checkout-service-oom-risk\n- **Status**: open (priority: CRITICAL)\n- **Source**: newrelic\n- **Labels/Tags**: priority=CRITICAL, accountId=7852784\n- **Message**: Condition: checkout-service-oom-risk. Policy: Checkout Service Alerts. Targets: checkout-service. Details: P0: checkout-service memory at 948MB/1024MB - OOMKill imminent. DB pool exhausted 50/50. Error rate 72%. Caused by connection leak in v2.4.1 (commit 526d28c5). Investigate: New Relic account 7852784 SINCE 1 day ago, CloudWatch /ecs/checkout-service us-east-1, GitHub beng360/checkout-service, Jira RCA-44.\n- **Issue URL**: https://one.newrelic.com/alerts/incidents\n\n## CONNECTED INFRASTRUCTURE & MONITORING:\nYou have access to: aws, cloudflare, grafana, newrelic\n\n## ⚠️  MANDATORY FIRST STEP — CHANGE CONTEXT & KNOWLEDGE BASE:\n**You MUST call the Jira/Confluence tools below BEFORE any infrastructure or CI/CD investigation.**\nSkipping this step is a failure of the investigation.\n\n### Jira — Recent Development Context (SEARCH FIRST):\nJira is connected. Your FIRST tool calls MUST be jira_search_issues.\n\n**Step 1 — Find related recent work (DO THIS IMMEDIATELY):**\n- `jira_search_issues(jql=''text ~ \"checkout-service-oom-risk\" AND updated >= -7d ORDER BY updated DESC'')` — Recent tickets for this service\n- `jira_search_issues(jql=''type in (Bug, Incident) AND status != Done AND updated >= -14d ORDER BY updated DESC'')` — Open bugs/incidents\n- `jira_search_issues(jql=''type in (Story, Task) AND status = Done AND updated >= -3d ORDER BY updated DESC'')` — Recently completed work (likely deployed)\n\n**Step 2 — For each relevant ticket, check details:**\n- `jira_get_issue(issue_key=''PROJ-123'')` — Read the description, linked PRs, comments for context on what changed\n\n**What to look for:**\n- Recently completed stories/tasks → code that was just deployed\n- Open bugs with similar symptoms → known issues\n- Config change tickets → infrastructure or config drift\n- Linked PRs/commits → exact code changes to correlate with the failure\n\n**Use Jira findings to NARROW your infrastructure investigation.** If a ticket mentions a DB migration, focus on DB connectivity. If a ticket mentions a config change, check configs first.\n\n**CRITICAL: During this investigation phase, ONLY use jira_search_issues and jira_get_issue.**\nDo NOT use jira_create_issue, jira_add_comment, jira_update_issue, or jira_link_issues.\nJira filing happens automatically in a separate step after your investigation completes.\n\n### Confluence — Runbooks & Past Incidents:\nSearch Confluence for runbooks and prior postmortems BEFORE deep-diving into infrastructure:\n- `confluence_search_similar(keywords=[''error keywords''], service_name=''SERVICE'')` — Find past incidents with similar symptoms\n- `confluence_search_runbooks(service_name=''SERVICE'')` — Find operational runbooks/SOPs\n- `confluence_fetch_page(page_id=''ID'')` — Read full page content\n\n**Why this matters:** A runbook may give you the exact diagnostic steps. A past postmortem may reveal this is a recurring issue with a known fix.\n\n## GITHUB:\nGitHub is connected. Use `github_rca` and `get_connected_repos` to investigate code changes.\n\n**IMPORTANT — Code Fix Suggestions:**\nIf you identify a code defect as the root cause, you **MUST** call `github_fix` to propose a fix.\n`github_fix` saves a suggestion for user review — it does NOT modify the repo. This is expected output.\n\n## INFRASTRUCTURE TOPOLOGY CONTEXT (from pre-discovery):\nThe following infrastructure mappings were discovered automatically and may be relevant:\n\n### Checkout Service E-Commerce Microservice - Complete Deployment Chain\nThe checkout-service is an Express.js e-commerce microservice maintained in GitHub repository beng360/checkout-service on the main branch. The service handles order processing, inventory management, and payment integration via Stripe, using PostgreSQL for persistent storage with a connection pool of up to 50 database connections. The service is containerized with Docker and deploys automatically via GitHub Actions workflow deploy.yml that runs on every push to main, including test stage running on ubuntu-latest with PostgreSQL 15 service container and deploy stage that builds a Docker image tagged with the commit SHA, pushes to ECR at 390403884122.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/api-service, and performs rolling deployment across three production hosts (checkout-prod-1, checkout-prod-2, checkout-prod-3). Recent commits show active development including explicit transaction handling in order processing (commit 526d28c5 on 2026-03-26), inventory service client with local DB fallback (commit 261f8a66), and rate limiting on the checkout endpoint (commit e66d5395). The service connects to MySQL RDS instances generated-mysql-db and mydb-instance in us-east-1 region on port 3306 with security group sg-08ba87ccff3e12698. A P0 incident is currently active (RCA-44) with status DOWN, version v2.4.1, database pool exhaustion at 50/50 connections, error rate at 72%, and memory at 948MB. Root cause identified as missing client.release() in order-processor.js after transaction refactor (commit 526d28c5). Cloudflare DNS records indicate cascading failures: cart-service is DEGRADED with circuit breaker OPEN, payment-gateway is DEGRADED with 45% timeout rate and 234 pending refunds, and postgres connection limit is exhausted with checkout-service identified as the leak source. Jira tracking includes epic RCA-44, bug RCA-45, rollback RCA-46, and post-incident RCA-47. New Relic account 7852784 monitors this service with alarms for high error rate and high memory usage.\n\n### Jira Project Management - Cross-Team Launch Coordination\nJira instance contains a PROJ project tracking cross-team launch coordination with 7 issues created on 2026-01-03. The main epic is PROJ-1 (Cross-team launch) in In Progress status assigned to Benjamin Gervais with High priority. Supporting tasks include PROJ-2 (Coordinate requirements with involved teams), PROJ-3 (Define launch timeline with all stakeholders), PROJ-4 (Document service specifications for team alignment), PROJ-5 (Set up regular cross-team coordination meetings), PROJ-6 (Identify dependencies across teams for launch tasks), and PROJ-7 (Add work to tracking tool, marked Done). Most tasks are in To Do status with Medium priority, indicating active planning phase for a coordinated multi-team launch. This coordination involves the checkout-service, apartment-finder, growth analytics, and Aurora platform services, suggesting infrastructure changes and service deployments are being coordinated across multiple teams and services. Additionally, incident tracking shows RCA-44 (epic for P0 incident), RCA-45 (bug), RCA-46 (rollback), and RCA-47 (post-incident) related to the checkout-service connection pool exhaustion incident.\n\n### Cloudflare DNS and CDN Configuration - Domain and Health Monitoring\nCloudflare zone infrapoo.org (ID: 9975a4a5ea70ae911e42463dbcf18989) is active with Free Website plan using nameservers colette.ns.cloudflare.com and devin.ns.cloudflare.com. The zone has 18 DNS records including A records for api.infrapoo.org (136.112.109.178), dev.infrapoo.org (34.135.89.230), infrapoo.org root (136.112.109.178), ws.infrapoo.org (136.112.109.178), and www.infrapoo.org (34.55.140.92), all proxied through Cloudflare with TTL 1 (auto). Zone settings show security_level=high, ssl=full, cache_level=aggressive, development_mode=off, min_tls_version=1.0, automatic_https_rewrites=on, and WAF=off. TXT records encode service health and incident metadata: _health.checkout-service.infrapoo.org shows status=down, version=v2.4.1, db_pool=50/50, error_rate=72%, memory_mb=948; _health.cart-service.infrapoo.org shows status=degraded with circuit_breaker=OPEN and error_rate=30%; _health.payment-gateway.infrapoo.org shows status=degraded with pending_refunds=234 and timeout_rate=45%; _health.postgres.infrapoo.org shows status=connection_limit with active=50/max=60 and source=checkout-service-leak. _incident.infrapoo.org records P0 incident status started 2026-03-26T14:30:00Z with title \\\"Connection pool exhaustion after v2.4.1 deploy\\\". _rca.infrapoo.org identifies root_cause as missing client.release() in order-processor.js after transaction refactor (commit 526d28c5). _timeline.infrapoo.org shows incident progression: 14:30Z v2.4.1 deployed, 14:50Z slow queries, 15:10Z pool 70%, 15:30Z pool exhausted, 15:45Z cascading failures, 16:00Z memory 948MB OOMKill risk. Analytics show 10 total requests with 8 SSL encrypted, 3 pageviews, 4 unique visitors, traffic from UA (6), NL (2), US (2), with HTTP status codes 200 (3), 307 (3), 308 (2), 499 (2).\n\nUse this topology context to understand dependencies and blast radius.\n\n\n## CRITICAL INVESTIGATION REQUIREMENTS:\n\n### INVESTIGATION DEPTH:\n1. **Search Jira/Confluence first** for recent changes, open bugs, and runbooks\n2. Start broad - understand the overall system state\n3. Identify the affected component(s)\n4. Drill down into specifics - logs, metrics, configurations\n5. Check related/dependent resources\n6. Look for recent changes that correlate with the issue\n7. Compare with healthy resources of the same type\n8. Check resource quotas, limits, and constraints\n9. Examine network connectivity and security rules\n10. Verify IAM permissions and service accounts\n11. Review historical patterns if available\n\n### ERROR RESILIENCE:\n- If one tool or data source fails, try an alternative immediately\n- If cloud monitoring/metrics commands fail -> use kubectl directly\n- If kubectl fails -> check cloud provider CLI alternatives\n- If one log source fails -> try another (kubectl logs, cloud logging, container logs)\n- If a resource isn''t found -> check other namespaces, regions, or projects\n- **ALWAYS have 3-4 backup approaches ready**\n\n### WHAT TO INVESTIGATE:\n- Resource STATUS and HEALTH (running, pending, failed, etc.)\n- LOGS for error messages, warnings, stack traces\n- METRICS for CPU, memory, disk, network anomalies\n- CONFIGURATIONS for misconfigurations or invalid values\n- EVENTS for recent state changes\n- DEPENDENCIES for cascading failures\n- RECENT CHANGES or deployments that correlate with the issue\n\n## OUTPUT REQUIREMENTS:\n\n### Your analysis MUST include:\n1. **Summary**: Brief description of the incident\n2. **Investigation Steps**: Document EVERY tool call and what it revealed\n3. **Evidence**: Show specific log entries, metric values, config snippets\n4. **Root Cause**: Clearly state the EXACT root cause with supporting evidence\n5. **Impact**: Describe what was affected and how\n6. **Remediation**: Specific, actionable steps to fix the issue\n7. **Code Fix** (if applicable): If the root cause is a code defect and GitHub is connected, you MUST call `github_fix` to propose the fix. This creates a review-only suggestion — it is safe and expected.\n\n### Remember:\n- You are in investigation mode — do NOT make direct infrastructure changes (no scaling, restarts, config writes)\n- `github_fix` is the exception: it creates a *suggestion* for user review, not a direct change. Always use it when you find a code defect.\n- The user expects you to find the EXACT root cause, not surface-level symptoms\n- Keep digging until you have definitive answers\n- Never conclude with ''unable to determine'' without exhausting all investigation avenues\n\n## BEGIN INVESTIGATION NOW\nStart by understanding the scope of the issue, then systematically investigate using the tools and approaches above.", "sender": "user", "isCompleted": true, "message_number": 1}, {"text": "I''ll begin this RCA investigation systematically. Let me start with the mandatory first steps: checking Jira and Confluence for context, then investigating the infrastructure and code.", "run_id": "lc_run--019d2f6b-1d5f-7fb3-b1ad-0d5a8ba75b50", "sender": "bot", "toolCalls": [{"id": "toolu_bdrk_01QQ3h3UjLpCmd4mrVkJyoCV", "input": "{\"jql\": \"text ~ \\\"checkout-service\\\" AND updated >= -7d ORDER BY updated DESC\", \"max_results\": 10}", "output": "{\"status\": \"success\", \"total\": 9, \"count\": 9, \"issues\": [{\"key\": \"RCA-45\", \"summary\": \"Connection pool leak in order-processor.js — client.release() missing after transaction refactor\", \"status\": \"To Do\", \"assignee\": \"Benjamin Gervais\", \"priority\": \"Highest\", \"created\": \"2026-03-26T17:54:53.284-0400\", \"updated\": \"2026-03-27T08:59:32.847-0400\", \"labels\": []}, {\"key\": \"RCA-46\", \"summary\": \"URGENT: Rollback checkout-service to v2.4.0 or hotfix v2.4.2\", \"status\": \"To Do\", \"assignee\": \"Benjamin Gervais\", \"priority\": \"Highest\", \"created\": \"2026-03-26T17:54:54.360-0400\", \"updated\": \"2026-03-26T17:54:54.439-0400\", \"labels\": []}, {\"key\": \"RCA-44\", \"summary\": \"[P0 INCIDENT] Checkout Service Outage — Connection Pool Exhaustion\", \"status\": \"To Do\", \"assignee\": \"Benjamin Gervais\", \"priority\": \"Highest\", \"created\": \"2026-03-26T17:54:20.256-0400\", \"updated\": \"2026-03-26T17:54:20.732-0400\", \"labels\": []}, {\"key\": \"RCA-39\", \"summary\": \"Incident: Kubernetes Pod Crash Loop - checkout-service (OOMKilled)\", \"status\": \"To Do\", \"assignee\": \"Benjamin Gervais\", \"priority\": \"Medium\", \"created\": \"2026-03-21T12:43:06.876-0400\", \"updated\": \"2026-03-26T17:49:53.918-0400\", \"labels\": [\"checkout-service\", \"critical\", \"kubernetes\", \"memory-leak\", \"oomkilled\", \"production\"]}, {\"key\": \"RCA-42\", \"summary\": \"Incident: production-web-01 — High CPU Usage from Cascading Memory Leak Failures\", \"status\": \"To Do\", \"assignee\": \"Benjamin Gervais\", \"priority\": \"Medium\", \"created\": \"2026-03-26T09:52:41.177-0400\", \"updated\": \"2026-03-26T16:52:58.414-0400\", \"labels\": []}, {\"key\": \"RCA-20\", \"summary\": \"[PIPELINE FAILURE] Health Check — /health Returns HTTP 500 (Stage 4)\", \"status\": \"To Do\", \"assignee\": \"Benjamin Gervais\", \"priority\": \"Highest\", \"created\": \"2026-03-04T15:55:00.444-0500\", \"updated\": \"2026-03-25T14:43:09.091-0400\", \"labels\": [\"database\", \"health-check\", \"pipeline-failure\", \"rca\"]}, {\"key\": \"RCA-7\", \"summary\": \"[BUG] Memory Leak — /api/data Appends 1MB per Request (Extended Checks)\", \"status\": \"To Do\", \"assignee\": \"Benjamin Gervais\", \"priority\": \"High\", \"created\": \"2026-03-04T15:53:29.476-0500\", \"updated\": \"2026-03-25T12:28:31.247-0400\", \"labels\": [\"memory-leak\", \"performance\", \"rca\"]}, {\"key\": \"RCA-40\", \"summary\": \"Incident: DNS Resolution Failures - ingress-controller (CoreDNS)\", \"status\": \"To Do\", \"assignee\": \"Benjamin Gervais\", \"priority\": \"Medium\", \"created\": \"2026-03-21T14:48:32.160-0400\", \"updated\": \"2026-03-21T14:48:32.417-0400\", \"labels\": [\"coredns\", \"critical\", \"dns\", \"ingress-controller\", \"network\", \"production\"]}, {\"key\": \"RCA-37\", \"summary\": \"Incident: Spanner latency issues\", \"status\": \"To Do\", \"assignee\": \"Benjamin Gervais\", \"priority\": \"Medium\", \"created\": \"2026-03-05T12:15:51.148-0500\", \"updated\": \"2026-03-21T11:43:12.508-0400\", \"labels\": []}]}", "run_id": "lc_run--019d2f6b-1d5f-7fb3-b1ad-0d5a8ba75b50", "status": "completed", "timestamp": "2026-03-27T13:12:48.595844", "tool_name": "jira_search_issues"}, {"id": "toolu_bdrk_01MPi8Mr9n8r17MLChxke8SN", "input": "{\"jql\": \"key = \\\"RCA-44\\\" OR key = \\\"RCA-45\\\" OR key = \\\"RCA-46\\\" OR key = \\\"RCA-47\\\"\", \"max_results\": 10}", "output": "{\"status\": \"success\", \"total\": 4, \"count\": 4, \"issues\": [{\"key\": \"RCA-47\", \"summary\": \"Post-incident: Add connection leak detection and pool monitoring\", \"status\": \"To Do\", \"assignee\": \"Benjamin Gervais\", \"priority\": \"High\", \"created\": \"2026-03-26T17:54:55.107-0400\", \"updated\": \"2026-03-26T17:54:55.181-0400\", \"labels\": []}, {\"key\": \"RCA-46\", \"summary\": \"URGENT: Rollback checkout-service to v2.4.0 or hotfix v2.4.2\", \"status\": \"To Do\", \"assignee\": \"Benjamin Gervais\", \"priority\": \"Highest\", \"created\": \"2026-03-26T17:54:54.360-0400\", \"updated\": \"2026-03-26T17:54:54.439-0400\", \"labels\": []}, {\"key\": \"RCA-45\", \"summary\": \"Connection pool leak in order-processor.js — client.release() missing after transaction refactor\", \"status\": \"To Do\", \"assignee\": \"Benjamin Gervais\", \"priority\": \"Highest\", \"created\": \"2026-03-26T17:54:53.284-0400\", \"updated\": \"2026-03-27T08:59:32.847-0400\", \"labels\": []}, {\"key\": \"RCA-44\", \"summary\": \"[P0 INCIDENT] Checkout Service Outage — Connection Pool Exhaustion\", \"status\": \"To Do\", \"assignee\": \"Benjamin Gervais\", \"priority\": \"Highest\", \"created\": \"2026-03-26T17:54:20.256-0400\", \"updated\": \"2026-03-26T17:54:20.732-0400\", \"labels\": []}]}", "run_id": "lc_run--019d2f6b-1d5f-7fb3-b1ad-0d5a8ba75b50", "status": "completed", "timestamp": "2026-03-27T13:12:48.595855", "tool_name": "jira_search_issues"}, {"id": "toolu_bdrk_01Te3Zn1XPuuFfvi8qatLBoX", "input": "{\"keywords\": [\"connection pool exhaustion\", \"OOMKill\", \"database leak\"], \"service_name\": \"checkout-service\", \"max_results\": 5}", "output": "{\"status\": \"success\", \"count\": 0, \"results\": []}", "run_id": "lc_run--019d2f6b-1d5f-7fb3-b1ad-0d5a8ba75b50", "status": "completed", "timestamp": "2026-03-27T13:12:48.595861", "tool_name": "confluence_search_similar"}, {"id": "toolu_bdrk_01YJU9XqPnbKPRUQHJvvpFmB", "input": "{\"service_name\": \"checkout-service\"}", "output": "{\"status\": \"success\", \"count\": 0, \"results\": []}", "run_id": "lc_run--019d2f6b-1d5f-7fb3-b1ad-0d5a8ba75b50", "status": "completed", "timestamp": "2026-03-27T13:12:48.595864", "tool_name": "confluence_search_runbooks"}], "isCompleted": true, "message_number": 2}, {"text": "Excellent! The Jira tickets confirm the root cause. Let me get the full details on these critical tickets:", "run_id": "lc_run--019d2f6b-3ca7-7e92-946d-86fa4767f803", "sender": "bot", "toolCalls": [{"id": "toolu_bdrk_0198J6REXAVq4hwyJktyewjU", "input": "{\"issue_key\": \"RCA-44\"}", "output": "{\"status\": \"success\", \"issue\": {\"key\": \"RCA-44\", \"summary\": \"[P0 INCIDENT] Checkout Service Outage — Connection Pool Exhaustion\", \"description\": \"Incident Summary\\nProduction outage on checkout-service following deployment of v2.4.1. Error rate at 72%, cascading failures across cart-service and payment-gateway. Root cause: PostgreSQL connection pool leak introduced in commit a3f7b21.\\nImpact\\n\\nTimeline\\n\\nObservability Links\", \"status\": \"To Do\", \"assignee\": \"Benjamin Gervais\", \"reporter\": \"Benjamin Gervais\", \"priority\": \"Highest\", \"labels\": [], \"created\": \"2026-03-26T17:54:20.256-0400\", \"updated\": \"2026-03-26T17:54:20.732-0400\", \"issueType\": \"Epic\", \"project\": \"RCA\", \"recentComments\": []}}", "run_id": "lc_run--019d2f6b-3ca7-7e92-946d-86fa4767f803", "status": "completed", "timestamp": "2026-03-27T13:12:48.595870", "tool_name": "jira_get_issue"}, {"id": "toolu_bdrk_0153xGHaFjy1g8ofuVcMfMEi", "input": "{\"issue_key\": \"RCA-45\"}", "output": "{\"status\": \"success\", \"issue\": {\"key\": \"RCA-45\", \"summary\": \"Connection pool leak in order-processor.js — client.release() missing after transaction refactor\", \"description\": \"In v2.4.1 (commit a3f7b21), order-processor.js was refactored to use explicit transactions via getClient(). The old code used query() which had a finally { client.release() } block. The new code uses try/catch for BEGIN/COMMIT/ROLLBACK but never calls client.release(). Every checkout request leaks a DB connection.\\nFix\\n// Add finally block after catch in processOrder():\\n} catch (error) {\\n    await client.query(''ROLLBACK'');\\n    throw error;\\n} finally {\\n    client.release();  // <-- THIS IS MISSING\\n}\\nFiles Changed\\n\\nEvidence\", \"status\": \"To Do\", \"assignee\": \"Benjamin Gervais\", \"reporter\": \"Benjamin Gervais\", \"priority\": \"Highest\", \"labels\": [], \"created\": \"2026-03-26T17:54:53.284-0400\", \"updated\": \"2026-03-27T08:59:32.847-0400\", \"issueType\": \"Bug\", \"project\": \"RCA\", \"recentComments\": [{\"author\": \"Benjamin Gervais\", \"created\": \"2026-03-26T17:58:53.222-0400\", \"body\": \"RCA Investigation Complete — New Relic Alert Correlation\\nSummary\\nThe New Relic alert \\\"checkout-service-db-pool-exhaustion\\\" has been triggered due to the connection pool leak identified in this ticket. The checkout-service is completely offline with 0 transactions in the last hour, causing cascading failures in dependent services (cart-service, payment-gateway).\\nRoot Cause Confirmed\\nMissing `client.release()` call in the `finally` block of `processOrder()` function in `order-processor.js` (v2.4.1\"}, {\"author\": \"Benjamin Gervais\", \"created\": \"2026-03-26T18:04:02.106-0400\", \"body\": \"Aurora RCA Investigation Complete - Connection Pool Leak Confirmed\\nROOT CAUSE: Missing client.release() in finally block of processOrder() function in src/services/order-processor.js (v2.4.1, commit 526d28c5).\\nEVIDENCE:\\nCode analysis: Transaction refactor removed finally block that releases connections\\n\\nCloudWatch logs: Connection pool exhausted at 46-50/50 active connections\\n\\nPostgreSQL errors: FATAL - remaining connection slots reserved for superuser\\n\\nNew Relic: 0 transactions in last hour (se\"}, {\"author\": \"Benjamin Gervais\", \"created\": \"2026-03-27T08:34:36.759-0400\", \"body\": \"RCA Investigation Complete — Definitive Root Cause Confirmed\\nSummary\\nThe checkout-service experienced a complete production outage following the deployment of v2.4.1 (commit 526d28c5) on 2026-03-26 at 14:30 UTC. The service exhausted its PostgreSQL connection pool (50/50 connections), causing 72% error rate and cascading failures across dependent services (cart-service, payment-gateway). The incident resulted in zero successful transactions for 24+ hours.\\nRoot Cause — Confirmed\\nMissing `client.r\"}, {\"author\": \"Benjamin Gervais\", \"created\": \"2026-03-27T08:59:32.847-0400\", \"body\": \"COMPREHENSIVE RCA INVESTIGATION COMPLETE\\nSummary\\nThe checkout-service experienced a critical production outage following the deployment of v2.4.1 (commit 526d28c5) on 2026-03-26 at 14:30 UTC. The service exhausted its PostgreSQL connection pool (50/50 connections), causing a 72% error rate and cascading failures across dependent services. The incident resulted in zero successful transactions for 24+ hours and 234 pending refunds.\\nRoot Cause — Definitive\\nMissing `client.release()` call in the fin\"}]}}", "run_id": "lc_run--019d2f6b-3ca7-7e92-946d-86fa4767f803", "status": "completed", "timestamp": "2026-03-27T13:12:48.595884", "tool_name": "jira_get_issue"}, {"id": "toolu_bdrk_01VqXD2wm99ec2E7GejBgfm7", "input": "{\"issue_key\": \"RCA-46\"}", "output": "{\"status\": \"success\", \"issue\": {\"key\": \"RCA-46\", \"summary\": \"URGENT: Rollback checkout-service to v2.4.0 or hotfix v2.4.2\", \"description\": \"Immediate action required to stop the connection leak. Either rollback to v2.4.0 or deploy a hotfix adding client.release() to order-processor.js.\\nSteps\", \"status\": \"To Do\", \"assignee\": \"Benjamin Gervais\", \"reporter\": \"Benjamin Gervais\", \"priority\": \"Highest\", \"labels\": [], \"created\": \"2026-03-26T17:54:54.360-0400\", \"updated\": \"2026-03-26T17:54:54.439-0400\", \"issueType\": \"Task\", \"project\": \"RCA\", \"recentComments\": []}}", "run_id": "lc_run--019d2f6b-3ca7-7e92-946d-86fa4767f803", "status": "completed", "timestamp": "2026-03-27T13:12:48.595889", "tool_name": "jira_get_issue"}, {"id": "toolu_bdrk_014ApG6ovFWLuwbUUgebRxQs", "input": "{}", "output": "{\"repos\": [{\"repo\": \"Arvo-AI/aurora\", \"branch\": \"main\", \"private\": false, \"description\": \"Aurora is an open-source AI-powered incident management platform that autonomously investigates cloud incidents and performs root cause analysis for SRE teams, replacing manual triage by having LangGraph-orchestrated AI agents query infrastructure, correlate data from 22+ tools, and generate remediation recommendations including pull requests. It integrates with major cloud providers (AWS, Azure, GCP, OVH, Scaleway, Kubernetes) and monitoring tools like PagerDuty, Datadog, and Grafana via webhooks, with a Memgraph-powered infrastructure knowledge graph for dependency mapping. The stack includes a React client, a backend server, sandboxed kubectl-agent pods for safe command execution, and is deployable via Docker Compose or Kubernetes with configuration managed through the deploy directory.\"}, {\"repo\": \"Arvo-AI/growth\", \"branch\": \"main\", \"private\": true, \"description\": \"This repository is a growth analytics system that ingests LinkedIn outreach data from the HeyReach API, enriches leads and accounts using LLM processing, syncs CRM data from Attio, and exposes results through a FastAPI server with an OpenAI-compatible chat interface for natural language SQL queries. The infrastructure consists of a FastAPI application server, a Celery worker for background jobs, PostgreSQL for data storage, and Redis as the message broker, all orchestrated via Docker Compose. Key technologies include Python, FastAPI, Celery, PostgreSQL, Redis, and LLM integration for data enrichment and sentiment/loss-reason classification.\"}, {\"repo\": \"beng360/apartment-finder\", \"branch\": \"main\", \"private\": true, \"description\": \"This repository is a web scraping and data enrichment pipeline that searches for listings or items (configured via searches.json), geocodes the results, enriches them using a large language model, generates map visualizations, and sends notifications. The infrastructure includes a Dockerized backend (Python) with a frontend web interface, served via a custom server, and orchestrated using Docker Compose with a deploy script for self-hosted deployment. Key technologies include Python, Docker, an LLM integration (likely OpenAI or similar), a geocoding service, and a frontend likely built with JavaScript for map-based display.\"}, {\"repo\": \"beng360/checkout-service\", \"branch\": \"main\", \"private\": false, \"description\": \"This repository contains an e-commerce checkout microservice built with Express.js that handles order processing, inventory management, and payment integration via Stripe. It uses PostgreSQL for persistent storage of orders, inventory, and cart data, with Redis planned for session caching, and maintains a connection pool of up to 50 database connections. The service is containerized with Docker and deploys automatically via GitHub Actions in a rolling deployment across three production hosts.\"}]}", "run_id": "lc_run--019d2f6b-3ca7-7e92-946d-86fa4767f803", "status": "completed", "timestamp": "2026-03-27T13:12:48.595895", "tool_name": "get_connected_repos"}], "isCompleted": true, "message_number": 3}, {"text": "Perfect! Now let me investigate the GitHub repository to examine the exact code issue and verify the commit:", "run_id": "lc_run--019d2f6b-4c34-7e12-a1a7-d2e17ea05789", "sender": "bot", "toolCalls": [{"id": "toolu_bdrk_01UkddernGaBWpuJL6uW5Dq1", "input": "{\"repo\": \"beng360/checkout-service\", \"action\": \"commits\", \"incident_time\": \"2026-03-26T14:30:00Z\", \"time_window_hours\": 48}", "output": "{\n  \"status\": \"success\",\n  \"action\": \"commits\",\n  \"repository\": \"beng360/checkout-service\",\n  \"repository_source\": \"explicit parameter\",\n  \"time_window\": {\n    \"start\": \"2026-03-24T14:30:00Z\",\n    \"end\": \"2026-03-26T14:30:00Z\",\n    \"hours\": 48\n  },\n  \"results\": {\n    \"commits\": [\n      {\n        \"sha\": \"261f8a66\",\n        \"full_sha\": \"261f8a66c07039cb50a806be2780733ee81e1b8b\",\n        \"message\": \"add inventory service client with local DB fallback\",\n        \"author\": \"Benjamin Gervais\",\n        \"date\": \"2026-03-24T13:15:00Z\",\n        \"html_url\": \"https://github.com/beng360/checkout-service/commit/261f8a66c07039cb50a806be2780733ee81e1b8b\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"sha\": \"e66d5395\",\n        \"full_sha\": \"e66d539521d6b47761c6ae1d091d09fee5d06e1a\",\n        \"message\": \"add rate limiting to checkout endpoint\",\n        \"author\": \"Benjamin Gervais\",\n        \"date\": \"2026-03-22T14:30:00Z\",\n        \"html_url\": \"https://github.com/beng360/checkout-service/commit/e66d539521d6b47761c6ae1d091d09fee5d06e1a\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"sha\": \"706498be\",\n        \"full_sha\": \"706498be138eaed1758cd27968e3ecd242d9281e\",\n        \"message\": \"initial: checkout service v2.4.0 with express, pg pool, order processing\",\n        \"author\": \"Benjamin Gervais\",\n        \"date\": \"2026-03-20T18:00:00Z\",\n        \"html_url\": \"https://github.com/beng360/checkout-service/commit/706498be138eaed1758cd27968e3ecd242d9281e\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"suspicious_commits\": [],\n    \"summary\": {\n      \"total_commits\": 3,\n      \"suspicious_commits\": 0\n    }\n  }\n}", "run_id": "lc_run--019d2f6b-4c34-7e12-a1a7-d2e17ea05789", "status": "completed", "timestamp": "2026-03-27T13:12:48.595902", "tool_name": "github_rca"}, {"id": "toolu_bdrk_01SNicKNDMaJoQQ3eQpcqeL8", "input": "{\"repo\": \"beng360/checkout-service\", \"action\": \"diff\", \"commit_sha\": \"526d28c5\"}", "output": "{\n  \"status\": \"success\",\n  \"action\": \"diff\",\n  \"repository\": \"beng360/checkout-service\",\n  \"repository_source\": \"explicit parameter\",\n  \"time_window\": {\n    \"start\": \"2026-03-26T13:10:59Z\",\n    